headline: Want To Profit On Election Outcomes? Interactive Brokers Has A Way.
summary: Online trading stock Interactive Brokers is nearing the buy point of a flat base.  Interactive Brokers stock was added to the S&P 500 on Aug. 28.  Its trading platform gives customers the ability to trade stocks, options, futures, currencies, bonds and funds on 160 markets worldwide.
